<figureCitation id="F09F0E891C15FFCA0AD326084EC6FCE8" box="[751,900,837,863]" captionStart="FIGURES 42 – 44" captionStartId="17.[151,269,1169,1193]" captionTargetBox="[153,1429,209,1144]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[151,1436,194,1145]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 42 – 44. Cerbalus aravaensis n. sp. ♂, holotype, left palpus. 42. Mesal view. 43. Ventral view. 44. Retrolateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/178117/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
Figs. 
<number id="DE6C002B1C15FFCA0B0A26084EC6FCE8" box="[822,900,837,863]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="43.0" valueMax="44.0" valueMin="42.0">42–44</number>
</figureCitation>
). Tibia with one prolateral macroseta and a pointed, retrolateral, black apophysis with light-brown step-like boss at middle (
<figureCitation id="F09F0E891C15FFCA0C7E26204993FC30" box="[1090,1233,877,903]" captionStart="FIGURES 42 – 44" captionStartId="17.[151,269,1169,1193]" captionTargetBox="[153,1429,209,1144]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[151,1436,194,1145]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 42 – 44. Cerbalus aravaensis n. sp. ♂, holotype, left palpus. 42. Mesal view. 43. Ventral view. 44. Retrolateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/178117/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Figs. 42, 43</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
