<paragraph id="681B120C1C15FFCA08FA21584991FBC9" blockId="16.[151,1437,341,1886]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<taxonomicName id="AFA4698F1C15FFCA08FA21584C7FFB99" box="[198,317,1045,1070]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Epigynum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="5AD0CE1E1C15FFCA08FA21584C7FFB99" box="[198,317,1045,1070]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Epigynum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Large. Smooth, cream-coloured median platelet posteriorly, at middle, slightly or deeply notched; sides bordered by dark brown raised folds densely covered with bristles (
<figureCitation id="F09F0E891C15FFCA0C59217149FCFBE1" box="[1125,1214,1084,1110]" captionStart="FIGURES 45, 46" captionStartId="17.[151,269,1952,1976]" captionTargetBox="[170,1432,1281,1922]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[151,1436,1253,1941]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 45, 46. Cerbalus aravaensis n. sp. Ψ. 45. Epigynum, ventral view. 46. Spermathecae, dorsal (inner) view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/178118/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
Fig. 
<number id="DE6C002B1C15FFCA0CA1217149FCFBE1" box="[1181,1214,1084,1110]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="45.0">45</number>
</figureCitation>
). Inner spermathecae consist of thick, blackish tubes partly hidden under large ovoid, whitish bodies (
<figureCitation id="F09F0E891C15FFCA0C5221294985FBC9" box="[1134,1223,1124,1150]" captionStart="FIGURES 45, 46" captionStartId="17.[151,269,1952,1976]" captionTargetBox="[170,1432,1281,1922]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[151,1436,1253,1941]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 45, 46. Cerbalus aravaensis n. sp. Ψ. 45. Epigynum, ventral view. 46. Spermathecae, dorsal (inner) view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/178118/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
Fig. 
<number id="DE6C002B1C15FFCA0C9921294985FBC9" box="[1189,1223,1124,1150]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="46.0">46</number>
</figureCitation>
