<emphasis id="5AD0CE1E1C15FFCA097321DC4F01FB1D" box="[335,579,1169,1194]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Cerbalus aravaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="5AD0CE1E1C15FFCA0A7021DD4FD2FB1D" bold="true" box="[588,656,1168,1194]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="41E373651C15FFCA0A7021DD4FD2FB1D" box="[588,656,1168,1194]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
resembles 
<taxonomicName id="AFA4698F1C15FFCA0B2A21DC494AFB1D" authority="Levy" authorityName="Levy" box="[790,1032,1168,1194]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Cerbalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="psammodes">
<emphasis id="5AD0CE1E1C15FFCA0B2A21DC4E81FB1D" box="[790,963,1169,1194]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">C. psammodes</emphasis>
Levy
</taxonomicName>
by the narrow clypeal region and the light coloured opisthosoma but differs distinctly, also from all other 
<taxonomicName id="AFA4698F1C15FFCA0BDA21F44910FB65" box="[998,1106,1209,1234]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Cerbalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="5AD0CE1E1C15FFCA0BDA21F44910FB65" box="[998,1106,1209,1234]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Cerbalus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species, by the shape of the peculiar, median apophysis projecting from the male palpal tergum, and by the shape of the inner spermathecae of the female.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="20BE41871C15FFCA08FA20794F70FA29" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" type="distribution">
